Privacy Policy:

At dReader LLC, we are committed to protecting the privacy of our users. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and share personal data in connection with our mobile app, which is an NFT marketplace.

What data do we collect?

When you use our app, we collect certain personal data in order to provide our services. This includes:

    Wallet data: When you connect your wallet to our app, we collect your wallet address and any associated data that is stored on the blockchain. We also store additional data about your wallet in our database, such as which NFTs you have marked as favorites.

    Transaction data: When you buy or sell an NFT on our app, we collect data about the transaction, such as the price, the NFT ID (address), and the wallet addresses of the buyer and seller.

How do we use your data?

We use the data that we collect to provide our services and to improve the user experience. Specifically, we use your data to:

    Enable transactions: We use your wallet data and transaction data to facilitate NFT transactions on our app.

    Personalize the app: We use your data to personalize the app and to provide you with recommendations and other personalized content.

    Improve the app: We use data analytics to improve the app and to identify areas where we can make enhancements.

How do we share your data?

We do not share your personal data with third parties except as necessary to provide our services or as required by law.

We take the security of your personal data very seriously and implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Your personal data is stored in our secure servers and databases, which are protected by firewalls, access controls, and encryption. We regularly monitor and audit our security systems to ensure that they are working effectively and to identify and address any potential vulnerabilities or threats.

We also use an open source API that allows anyone to access and retrieve data from our database, including third-party services. However, we do not actively share user data with third-party services and take steps to protect user data from unauthorized access or misuse. We implement appropriate security measures, such as rate limiting, authentication and authorization mechanisms, and data encryption, to ensure that only authorized parties are able to access our data. Additionally, we do not sell or rent user data to third-party services. By using our platform, you acknowledge and agree that data submitted to our API may be accessed by third-party services, but that we are committed to protecting your data and maintaining your privacy.

Data transfers outside of the EU

Our servers are located across USA, EU, and Asia. If you are accessing our app from outside of the EU, your data may be transferred to and processed in a country outside of the EU.

GDPR Compliance

If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have certain data protection rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). We are committed to complying with the GDPR and ensuring that your personal data is processed in a lawful, fair, and transparent manner.

We only collect and process your personal data when it is necessary for the purposes outlined in this privacy policy. We will not process your personal data for any other purposes unless we have obtained your explicit consent to do so.

You have the right to access, rectify, or delete your personal data that we have collected or to restrict or object to its processing. You also have the right to data portability and the right to withdraw your consent at any time. To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided at the end of this privacy policy.

If you believe that we have not complied with your data protection rights, you have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.

Your rights

You have the right to access, rectify, and delete your personal data, as well as the right to object to its processing. To exercise these rights, please contact us at privacy@dreader.io.

Updates to this policy

We may update this privacy policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice in the app.

If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please contact us at privacy@dreader.io.